  { title: 'Samoa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/samoa' },
  { title: 'New Zealand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/new-zealand' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'tongaFit', header: 'Tonga Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TOP$1,000-1,430/mo', tongaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TOP$1,170-1,670/mo', tongaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TOP$900-1,285/mo', tongaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TOP$835-1,195/mo', tongaFit: 'Very Good' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'TOP$900-1,430', annual: 'TOP$10,800-17,160' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'TOP$1,235-1,905', annual: 'TOP$14,820-22,860' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'TOP$1,660-2,560', annual: 'TOP$19,920-30,720' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'TOP$80-200/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Evacuation to NZ', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'TOP$40,000-120,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tonga 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Tonga. Last Polynesian kingdom, whale watching, recovering from volcanic eruption, and coverage for retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tonga"
  subheadline="Tonga offers the last Polynesian kingdom, humpback whale watching, pristine islands, and traditional culture—recovering from the 2022 volcanic eruption, this resilient kingdom welcomes visitors to authentic Pacific life."
  heroImage="/images/countries/tonga-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Tonga</h2>
  <p>
    Tonga offers the unique distinction of being the Pacific's only remaining monarchy, spectacular humpback whale watching (July-October), pristine island groups, and genuine Polynesian culture. The 2022 Hunga Tonga volcanic eruption and tsunami caused significant damage, but Tonga is recovering with resilient spirit.
  </p>

  <p>
    Nuku'alofa (Tongatapu) is capital with most services. Vava'u is whale watching center. Ha'apai offers remote island experience. Population ~100,000. Auckland, New Zealand is 3.5 hours flight—primary medical backup.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Very limited; NZ evacuation essential</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Tongan, English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> TOP$2,500-5,000/month (~$1,050-2,100 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; cyclone season</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Royal; traditional; resilient</li>
      <li><strong>2022 Impact:</strong> Recovering from volcanic eruption</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Tonga Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Tonga healthcare is very limited—Vaiola Hospital (Nuku'alofa) is main facility but basic. Outer islands have minimal care. The 2022 volcanic eruption strained healthcare resources. Complex cases require evacuation to Auckland (3.5 hours) with excellent New Zealand hospitals.
  </p>

  <p>
    Auckland provides essential backup—Auckland City Hospital and private options. Strong NZ-Tonga ties facilitate medical travel. International insurance with NZ evacuation coverage absolutely essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">2022 Eruption Impact</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      The January 2022 Hunga Tonga-Hunga Ha'apai volcanic eruption and tsunami caused significant damage. Infrastructure is being rebuilt. Healthcare resources were strained. Verify current conditions. Tonga is resilient but recovery ongoing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Tonga visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Visitor Permit</h3>
  <p>
    31-day permit on arrival for most nationalities. Simple entry.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Visitor Permit</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions available for up to 6 months through Immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For long-term residence. Various categories. Apply through Immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Royal Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    Tonga remains a constitutional monarchy—King Tupou VI. Respectful behavior toward royalty expected.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Tonga:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Extended stay:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> New Zealand coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Natural disasters:</strong> Consider volcanic/cyclone coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Tonga</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with strong NZ evacuation essential. Local care very basic. Include natural disaster evacuation coverage given volcanic activity. Outer islands require helicopter evacuation consideration.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Tonga, evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Tonga</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Pacific network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>NZ access:</strong> Auckland 3.5 hours away</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation focus:</strong> Critical for remote islands</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Tonga with NZ evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Tonga (TOP ~2.37 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Nuku'alofa base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>NZ network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Affordable living:</strong> Low daily costs</li>
    <li><strong>Whale season:</strong> Visit July-October</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Whale Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month. Vava'u whale season. July-October visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with NZ coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TOP$1,050/month (~$440). Whale watching paradise; Auckland backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Tongan Diaspora, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> NZ$3,200/month. Family in Tonga. Extended visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with NZ/Tonga coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TOP$1,250/month (~$530). Family connection; NZ backup familiar.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Remote Island Life, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month. Ha'apai islands. Simple lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with helicopter evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TOP$950/month (~$400). Remote beauty; essential backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Has Tonga recovered from 2022?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Recovering—significant progress but ongoing. Infrastructure being rebuilt. Tourism returning. Some areas more affected than others. Verify current conditions. Tongans are remarkably resilient.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the whale watching like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Exceptional—humpback whales breed in Tonga July-October. Swimming with whales possible (with licensed operators). Vava'u is center. One of world's best whale watching experiences.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Tonga safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—low crime, welcoming culture. Royal kingdom with traditional values. Sunday strictly observed. Modest dress expected. Natural disasters (cyclones, volcanic activity) are primary concerns.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why Tonga over Fiji or Samoa?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Unique monarchy experience, best whale watching in Pacific, more remote and authentic. Fiji has better infrastructure. Samoa more affordable. Tonga for whales and royal culture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Tonga coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Tonga is recovering from 2022 volcanic eruption. Healthcare very limited—NZ evacuation essential. Verify current conditions before travel.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
